cs.PR, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.PL, cs.AR 

The paper is about pseudo-random number generators (PRNGs) and their statistical properties, which falls under the category of cs.PR (Computational Complexity). The paper also discusses the use of instruction-level parallelism in modern processors, which could fall under cs.PL (Programming Languages). The creation and testing of scaled-down versions of the generators could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper mentions the creation of multiple cycles with pseudo-random lengths, which could fall under cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
